==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pruning
<hw>Prun"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of trimming, or removing what is superfluous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Falconry)</fld> <def>That which is cast off by bird
in pruning her feathers; leavings.</def> <rj><au>Beau. &
Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Pruning hook</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Pruning
knife</b></col></mcol>, <cd>cutting instrument used in pruning trees,
etc.</cd> -- <col><b>Pruning shears</b></col>, <cd>shears for pruning
trees, vines, etc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prunus</ent>⟦br⟧
